                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-131-off722 t18270712-131-crimeloc725"></join>. On the 13th of June the prisoner took a room, and next morning, at a quarter-past nine o'clock, I heard him going down very slowly - I ran to the door, and thought I saw him; I went to his room, and missed the counterpane and sheets, which were safe at a quarter to eleven the night before. When he was apprehended I said, "I suppose you know me" - he said Yes.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Did he appear in want? A. No - he was respectably dressed. I was with my mother when he took the room; the property has not been found; I saw it safe at half-past eleven o'clock at night, when I drew the curtains.</p>
